</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1441,700,1077]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,700,724]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Definition.</emphasis>
A possible sister to the clade with 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[774,1055,700,724]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,851,700,724]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Thoon</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1072,1126,700,724]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1889" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Proteides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modius">
<emphasis box="[1229,1440,700,724]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Proteides modius</emphasis>
Mabille, 1889
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[427,726,732,756]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[427,524,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Halotus</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[741,795,732,756]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[895,1285,732,756]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxula">
<emphasis box="[895,1108,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Hesperilla saxula</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1886" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1886" box="[417,777,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angellus">
<emphasis box="[417,635,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Hesperia angellus</emphasis>
Plötz, 1886
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[800,931,764,789]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1234,1333,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Psoralis</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[266,320,797,821]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[420,799,796,821]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabaeus">
<emphasis box="[420,623,796,820]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Psoralis sabaeus</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, currently considered a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Weeks, 1901" authorityName="Weeks" authorityYear="1901" box="[192,535,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idee">
<emphasis box="[192,371,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Pamphila idee</emphasis>
Weeks, 1901
</taxonomicName>
) where it was placed previously (
<figureCitation box="[954,1087,828,853]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Immediately distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[260,359,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,359,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Psoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by greenish ventral colors and a pattern of four pale dots on hindwing below, indeed reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[377,454,892,916]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,454,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Thoon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Genitalia illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[770,900,893,917]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell (1959</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 24, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bell, 1959" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1959" box="[1041,1329,892,917]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1194,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Psoralis alis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[1202,1329,893,917]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell, 1959</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,674,924,948]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chittara">
<emphasis box="[484,674,924,948]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Chitta chittara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), quite distinctive and diagnostic: uncus and tegumen very short, look compressed, penis with a long titillator diverging from penis, valva peculiar, crooked with three teeth on harpe, directed dorsad, caudad and ventrad (
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[932,1053,989,1013]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell 1959</bibRefCitation>
). In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly 
<date box="[651,758,1021,1045]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" value="1107-09-06">1107.9.6</date>
:A335C, aly13410.7.2:T37C, aly 
<date box="[1142,1247,1021,1045]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" value="1838-08-03">1838.8.3</date>
:G730G (not C), aly127.64.1:G1182G (not A), aly4966.20.2:A1499A (not G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1440,1101,1126]" box="[192,1440,1101,1126]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,344,1101,1125]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular formed from the 
<typeStatus box="[1217,1269,1102,1126]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,707,1149,1174]" box="[192,707,1149,1174]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,1149,1173]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[553,606,1150,1174]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,823,1197,1221]" box="[192,823,1197,1221]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1197,1221]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[647,819,1197,1221]" journalOrPublisher="Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="642 - 676" part="24" refId="ref28580" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
